---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';

const locale = 'en';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Frame Picker By Kriss - Zero data collection, your privacy is our priority."
  locale={locale}
  canonicalPath="/privacy"
  lastUpdated="December 2024"
>
  <h2>Summary</h2>
  <p><strong>Frame Picker By Kriss does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data.</strong> The app operates entirely on your device and respects your privacy.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Information We Do NOT Collect</h2>
  <p>We want to be transparent: <strong>we do not collect any data from you</strong>. Specifically:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>No personal information</strong> - We don't ask for or store your name, email, or any identifying information</li>
    <li><strong>No usage analytics</strong> - We don't track how you use the app</li>
    <li><strong>No crash reports</strong> - We don't collect crash data or diagnostics</li>
    <li><strong>No location data</strong> - We don't access your location</li>
    <li><strong>No device identifiers</strong> - We don't collect device IDs or fingerprints</li>
    <li><strong>No cookies or tracking</strong> - The app doesn't use any tracking technologies</li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>Data That Stays on Your Device</h2>
  <p>All data created and used by Frame Picker By Kriss remains exclusively on your Mac:</p>

  <h3>Video Files</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Videos you open are processed locally on your device</li>
    <li>We never upload, copy, or transmit your video files anywhere</li>
    <li>Video file access is limited to files you explicitly select</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Exported Frames</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Extracted frames are saved only to the location you choose</li>
    <li>No copies are made elsewhere</li>
    <li>Files remain under your complete control</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Project Files (.fpk)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Project files are saved locally where you specify</li>
    <li>They contain only references to your videos and marker positions</li>
    <li>No project data is transmitted externally</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Preferences</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Your settings and preferences are stored locally in standard macOS preferences</li>
    <li>This includes language choice, default export format, and keyboard shortcuts</li>
    <li>These preferences never leave your device</li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>App Sandbox</h2>
  <p>Frame Picker By Kriss runs in Apple's App Sandbox, which means:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>The app can only access files you explicitly select through file pickers</li>
    <li>It cannot access arbitrary files on your system</li>
    <li>Network access is limited to App Store purchase verification</li>
    <li>Your data is isolated and protected</li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>In-App Purchases</h2>
  <p>When you make an in-app purchase to unlock the full version:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>The transaction is processed entirely by Apple through the App Store</li>
    <li>We do not receive or store any payment information</li>
    <li>We do not have access to your Apple ID, credit card, or billing details</li>
    <li>Apple's privacy policy governs how Apple handles purchase transactions</li>
  </ul>
  <p>For more information on how Apple handles your data, please see <a href="https://www.apple.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apple's Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>Frame Picker By Kriss does not use any third-party services, SDKs, or analytics platforms. The only external connection is to Apple's App Store for in-app purchase verification, which is handled by Apple's frameworks.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>Frame Picker By Kriss does not collect any data from anyone, including children under 13. The app is safe for users of all ages.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Data Security</h2>
  <p>Since we don't collect any data, there is no data to secure on our end. Your files and preferences remain on your device, protected by macOS security features including:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>App Sandbox isolation</li>
    <li>Hardened Runtime</li>
    <li>Gatekeeper verification</li>
    <li>System Integrity Protection</li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Updating the "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy</li>
    <li>Posting the new Privacy Policy on our website</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Your Rights</h2>
  <p>Since we don't collect any personal data:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>There is no data to access, correct, or delete</li>
    <li>There is no data to port or export</li>
    <li>There is no data processing to object to</li>
  </ul>
  <p>You have complete control over all data created by the app because it exists only on your device.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Contact Us</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us at:</p>
  <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@codebykriss.fr">contact@codebykriss.fr</a></p>
  <p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://framepickerbykriss.com/support">https://framepickerbykriss.com/support</a></p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Compliance</h2>
  <p>This app is designed to comply with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>GDPR</strong> (General Data Protection Regulation) - EU</li>
    <li><strong>CCPA</strong> (California Consumer Privacy Act) - California, USA</li>
    <li><strong>PIPEDA</strong> (Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act) - Canada</li>
    <li><strong>Apple App Store Guidelines</strong></li>
  </ul>
  <p>Since we collect no personal data, compliance with these regulations is straightforward.</p>

  <hr />

  <p><em>Frame Picker By Kriss - Your videos, your frames, your privacy.</em></p>
</LegalLayout>
